commitResults.messageTitle: Update MarkOrderCommand when order already marked
commitResults.messageBody:
* If attempting to mark an order that was already completed,
a new message is given to the user.
* Have changed the function from setIsComplete() to markComplete(),
since we do not allow undo of completion. The function will return
a boolean hasChanged informing the caller whether or not there
was a change made to the orders completed status.
* Testcases were updated

commitResults.messageTitle: Update MarkTaskCommand when task already marked
commitResults.messageBody:
* If attempting to mark an task that is already done,
a new message is given to the user.
* Have changed the function from setIsDone() to markDone(),
since we do not allow undo of completion. The function will return
a boolean hasChanged informing the caller whether or not there
was a change made to the task status.
* Testcases were updated

commitResults.messageBody:
UniqueTaskList mirrors the implementation of UniquePersonList.
The following main points are addressed:

* Task isSameTask() function added that checks for equality based
on label and tasktag
* Label equality now checks ignoring case. so Sew Buttons is the
same label as sew BUTTONS
* Storage functions updated to respect unique tasks requirement
* AddTaskCommandTest refactored
* UniqueTaskListTest added, mirroring UniquePersonListTest

* isValidAmount now checks if string is valid using
Double.parseDouble. It checks for NumberFormatException and deals
with it by returning false to notify user that input had errors.
* Updated AmountTest testcases to respect new method of parsing
* Updated CommandTestUtil invalid amount example
* Updated UG with notes about Amount format, and warning about
possible loss of precision

Made some other small necessary changes to test utility classes
and methods.

FindX commands no longer accept non-alphanumeric characters.
e.g. find !ab will fail.
